.TH "snd_pcm_format_set_silence" 9 "snd_pcm_format_set_silence" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
snd_pcm_format_set_silence \- set the silence data on the buffer
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" snd_pcm_format_set_silence
.BI "(snd_pcm_format_t format "  ","
.BI "void *data "  ","
.BI "unsigned int samples "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "format" 12
the PCM format
.IP "data" 12
the buffer pointer
.IP "samples" 12
the number of samples to set silence
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Sets the silence data on the buffer for the given samples.
.SH "RETURN"
Zero if successful, or a negative error code on failure.
